        <prompt>What was President Andrew Johnson's primary objection to the Freedmen's Bureau?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">He saw it as federal interference in state matters</option>
            <option letter="b">It was too expensive to maintain</option>
            <option letter="c">It didn't help enough people</option>
            <option letter="d">It had too much military control</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>Johnson opposed the Freedmen's Bureau because he believed it represented unconstitutional federal interference in matters that should be left to the states.</explanation>
