        <prompt>What role did African American churches play in education during Reconstruction?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">They often housed the first schools for freedmen</option>
            <option letter="b">They opposed educational initiatives</option>
            <option letter="c">They only provided religious education</option>
            <option letter="d">They focused on adult education only</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>African American churches often served as the first schoolhouses for freedmen, combining religious instruction with basic education and literacy programs.</explanation>
