        <prompt>What was the significance of the Civil Rights Cases of 1883?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Declared the Civil Rights Act of 1875 unconstitutional</option>
            <option letter="b">Strengthened federal civil rights protection</option>
            <option letter="c">Established voting rights</option>
            <option letter="d">Created new anti-discrimination laws</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The Supreme Court's decision in the Civil Rights Cases declared the Civil Rights Act of 1875 unconstitutional, severely limiting federal protection against private discrimination.</explanation>
